  "texts": [
    "• Enhanced Feature Representation using Residual Connections: The residual connections in the RCA network allow for effective multi-scale feature extraction without the risk of gradient vanishing.",
    "This structure improves the network's ability to capture both local and global spatial features, enhancing its capacity to learn complex relationships within the data.",
    "• Lightweight Channel-Attention Mechanism: The integration of a lightweight squeezeand-excitation (SE) channel-attention mechanism allows the RCA network to selectively emphasize important feature channels while suppressing irrelevant ones.",
    "This helps the model focus on key features that are crucial for accurate scene classification.Our approach involves extracting low-level, local features such as corners and edges using convolution operations in the network's shallower layers, followed by capturing global abstract semantic features using channel-attention module in the deeper layers.",
    "The last step involves inputting these distinguishing characteristics into the fully connected layer to predict the remote sensing scene category."
  ],
